To [[Freeze tracks|freeze a track]] in [[Ableton Live]] simply right click the track header (where the name of the track is) in either the [[Ableton Live:Toggle between session and arrange windows|session or arrange views]]. Choose '''Freeze''' from the pop up menu that appears.To unfreeze a track repeat this proceedure on the same track but choose '''Unfreeze''' from the pop up menu.

Once you feeeze a track you won't be able to edit it's effects but you can still move the audio (or MIDI) around.
If you would like to permanently "freeze" the track simpley right click the track header of a frozen track and choose '''Flatten''' 




